description: Talbert Tso Just in case you haven't heard, recently, a major flaw was announced for WPA-2 (Wifi Protection Access II); basically, the default security protocol for many devices that uses wifi. These includes devices such as: mobile phones, wireless internet routers, and others.  Majority of companies are aware of the problem and are rolling out update for your specific devices. Please make sure your devices are up to date; including updating firmware for your wireless routers.  Until a patch is ready for your device, please make sure you are using secure websites. This can be easily identified when you look up in the URL address bar and it starts with "https://" and NOT "http://" (the "s" makes the difference).
